		<h3>We Develop Developers</h3>
		<p>
			The founders of Big D Code met at a hackathon in 2014 where the majority of the participants did not know how to code. They decided that that was kind of messed up, and started developing curriculum to support anyone who wanted to learn how to code, collaborate, and develop useful apps.
		</p>
		<p>
			Today, Big D Code offers several different courses structured as three-month or six-month programs. The part-time programs are designed with the 9-to-5 grind in mind. It works just like any other night-school schedule. The full-time programs are designed uniquely to train students as full-stack developers. In the full-time programs, we also work on leadership, communication, and project management skills, in addition to the coding curriculum.
		</p>
		<p>
			Big D Code is housed within NoD (pronounced "node"), a collaborative coworking space in North Dallas. The location is super convenient for anyone based in Dallas, Plano, Frisco, McKinney, Richardson, Allen, Addison, Carrollton, Prosper, Farmers Branch, Southlake, or Grapevine. The coworking space is open 24/7 for members and Big D Code students and is fully equipped with training rooms, whiteboards, conference rooms, and of course, a ping pong table.
		</p>
		<h3>Why choose Big D Code?</h3>
		<h4>Refined Curriculum</h4>
		<p>
			Our curriculum has been vetted by industry experts and has been tested repeatedly in focus groups and 1-on-1 feedback sessions with private lesson students.
		</p>
		<h4>Employer Network</h4>
		<p>
			Big D Code students receive directly exposure to local employers and recruiters. Students not only particpate in portfolio workshops but also present their projects to employers during the portfolio show on the last day of classes.
		</p>
		<h4>Individual Attention</h4>
		<p>
			Each lesson consists of a lecture portion and a working session. During the working sessions, instructors will come by each student's computer to make sure they aren't getting stuck. Big D Code also strongly encourages pair-programming and we teach all of our students how to effectively 'pair' with one another during the program.
		</div>
